Bug #1

Bug Title: Product Card UI Misalignment on iPhone 12 Pro Viewport

Category / Type: UI / Responsive Design Issue

Field	Details
Bug Title	Product Card UI Misalignment on iPhone 12 Pro Viewport
Website Tested	(put website name here)
Environment	Desktop Chrome → Inspect → Responsive Mode → iPhone 12 Pro

Steps to Reproduce	
1. Open website
2. Open product listing page
3. Open DevTools → Responsive → select iPhone 12 Pro viewport
4. Observe spacing between images, text, and price

Actual Result	Images, product name text, and product price appear misaligned with large empty spaces; price appears too low from product image
Expected Result	UI elements should remain aligned correctly across different devices; price, text, and image should maintain consistent spacing layout

Severity: Low (because function still works but UI looks messy)

Bug #2

Bug Title: Missing Home navigation button inside Cart / Checkout page

Website Tested: (put here what site you testing)

Environment: Chrome DevTools – Mobile View (iPhone 12 Pro)

Steps to Reproduce:

Open the website

Add any product to cart

Go to Cart page then proceed to Checkout

Look for Home navigation button

Expected Result:
There should be a visible Home button or quick navigation option to return back to main homepage easily.

Actual Result:
No Home button exists on Cart / Checkout page. User needs to press Cancel or manually navigate back.

Severity: Low
(But can affect older users or non-tech users because they may not understand how to go back)
